OL,3,CThree people with incurable conditions
OL,4,Cshare views on assisted dying
OL,6,FLynne Cottignies is lying on a hospice
OL,7,Fbed.
OL,9,FHer stage four breast cancer is now
OL,10,Funtreatable and the end is near.
OL,12,FShe wanted to end her life when she
OL,13,Fchose, through an assisted death.
OL,15,F"It's just ridiculous that you don't
OL,16,Fhave the choice," she told me.
OL,18,FThree days later, Lynne died in that
OL,19,Fsame bed - just a week before Jersey
OL,20,Fpoliticians would debate whether to
OL,21,Fsupport her cause.
