OL,3,CThree people with incurable conditions
OL,4,Cshare views on assisted dying
OL,6,FLynne and may have been eligible as
OL,7,Fshe had a terminal illness with six
OL,8,Fmonths or less left to live.
OL,10,FHer husband Fred had supported her
OL,11,Fthrough her cancer and with this cause.
OL,13,F"People are going to get to a
OL,14,Fsituation where they're seriously ill,
OL,15,Fmaybe terminal, and if they decide
OL,16,F'that's enough, I want to end it', why
OL,17,Fon earth shouldn't they have that
OL,18,Fright?" he told me.
